    AI Overview
    Healthcare technology solutions for improving Star ratings and automating HEDIS reporting in 2025 focus on
    digital quality measures (dQM), Artificial Intelligence (AI), and enhanced interoperability using standards like FHIR and CQL . These technologies streamline data collection, improve accuracy, and enable proactive care management to boost performance.  
    Key Vendors 
    Several vendors offer certified solutions that align with the 2025 digital HEDIS and Star Ratings requirements. Health plans should use NCQA-validated digital solutions. 
    • Vitalis Offers Vitalis360 , a unified, cloud-based data and quality performance platform that automates HEDIS, Stars, and quality reporting workflows. Built for interoperability, the Vitalis360 platform supports digital quality measures (dQMs), ECDS reporting, and FHIR-based data ingestion from EHRs, HIEs, and registries.
    • Smile Digital Health: Provides a dQM for HEDIS solution that is FHIR-native, directly integrates digital measures from NCQA's DCS program, and automates quality evaluation in near real-time.
    • Epic: The Epic Value Based Analytics Module is an NCQA-certified solution for HEDIS reporting.
    • Inovalon and Cotiviti: Recognized as top vendors for their analytics, data integration, and quality measurement tools supporting HEDIS and Star ratings improvements.  
    Key Technology Solutions & Trends in 2025 
    1. Digital Quality Measures (dQM) and Interoperability 
    The primary shift in 2025 is the move to fully digital HEDIS reporting, which reduces the administrative burden of manual chart reviews.  
    • FHIR (Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources) and CQL (Clinical Quality Language): NCQA requires the collection and reporting of data using the FHIR open standard for data exchange and CQL for machine-readable measure logic. This standardization allows measure logic to be automated, consistent, and reliable, eliminating the need for repeatedly developed proprietary measures.
    • Electronic Clinical Data Systems (ECDS): ECDS allows health plans to pull data from diverse digital sources, including EHRs, Health Information Exchanges (HIEs), and registries. Several 2025 measures require ECDS-only reporting, such as Cervical Cancer Screening (CCS) and Childhood Immunization Status (CIS), phasing out the traditional hybrid approach.  
    2. Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML)  
    AI and ML are transforming quality improvement and reporting by analyzing vast amounts of data efficiently. 
    • Data Analysis and Predictive Analytics: AI analyzes historical and real-time data to identify high-risk patients, predict the likelihood of developing conditions, and pinpoint care gaps, allowing for proactive interventions.
    • Natural Language Processing (NLP): NLP is used for automated medical chart coding and extracting relevant information from unstructured data in EHRs, further reducing manual review efforts and improving data accuracy.
    • Automation of Administrative Tasks: AI automates routine tasks like claims processing, scheduling, and data entry, freeing up clinicians and quality teams to focus on patient interaction and complex cases.  
    3. Patient Engagement and Remote Monitoring Tools 
    Improving member satisfaction and engagement directly impacts HEDIS and Star scores (specifically CAHPS measures). 
    • Telehealth and Remote Patient Monitoring (RPM): Digital health solutions and IoMT (Internet of Medical Things) devices enable remote chronic disease monitoring, ensure timely follow-ups, and expand access to care for underserved populations.
    • Virtual Health Assistants and AI Chatbots: These tools provide personalized care recommendations, answer medical queries, send reminders for appointments/medications, and offer self-guided care navigation, enhancing member satisfaction and adherence to care plans.
    • Proxy Satisfaction Surveys: Embedded micro-surveys and in-platform feedback tools offer real-time insights into member satisfaction, serving as proxies for CAHPS scores.  
    • Digital Quality, Unified: Introducing Vitalis360
      Vitalis360 is a unified, cloud-based data and quality performance platform that automates HEDIS, Stars, and digital quality measures. Built on FHIR and ECDS, it streamlines reporting and reduces manual chart review.

    What is the difference between HEDIS and stars?
    HEDIS Ratings vs Star Ratings

    HEDIS is managed and defined by the NCQA and applies to essentially everyone in the healthcare space. Star ratings are more unique, since they're managed by CMS and apply only to Medicare Advantage plans.
